                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLFence",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " instance a pass updates to inform the GPU that it can begin running the applicable stages of the pass.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "fence"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "An ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLRenderStages",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " instance that designates which stages in the render pass apply to ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "fence",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": ".",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "stages"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Fences maintain order to prevent GPU data hazards as the GPU runs various passes, including render passes, within the same command queue. The render pass waits for a pass to update ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "fence",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " (see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLRenderCommandEncoder/updateFence(_:after:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ") before running any stage in the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "stages",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " parameter.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "For a render pass that updates and waits for the same fence, call ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLRenderCommandEncoder/waitForFence(_:before:)",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " only before calling ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLRenderCommandEncoder/updateFence(_:after:)",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": ". Updating a fence before waiting on it within the same encoder can cause GPU deadlock.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Important",
          "style": "important",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The GPU driver evaluates the passâ€™s fences and the commands that depend on them when your app commits the enclosing ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLCommandBuffer",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Apple family GPUs can update and respond to fences on a per-stage basis. That allows those GPUs to run portions of different stages, such as vertex and fragment, at the same time. You can check whether a GPU is in an Apple GPU family with the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.metal/documentation/Metal/MTLDevice/supportsFamily(_:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
